                    <msContents>
                        <summary>
                         It records that the temple administrators (<foreign>tēvakaṉmi</foreign>) and the <foreign>māheśvaras</foreign> should carry out the worshipping and food offering of Tiruvātavūr-Nāyaṉār (Māṇikkavācakar), whose image was installed by a certain Tiruveḷḷaṟai-cōkkaṉ Uyyavantāṉ, alias Sundara-pāṇṭiya-brahmatarāyaṉ. 
                        </summary> 
                    </msContents>
                    <physDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <p>No distinction between <foreign>e</foreign> and <foreign>ē</foreign>, <foreign>o</foreign> and <foreign>ō</foreign>.</p>
                        </handDesc>
                    </physDesc>
                </msDesc>
